get media item "MAY 2013" WordPress Codex "Function Reference"
==============================================================

NAME
----

get media item - Retrieve HTML form for modifying the image attachment.

SYNOPSIS
--------

Retrieve HTML form for modifying the image attachment.

USAGE
-----

` <?php get_media_item( $attachment_id, $args ); ?> `

PARAMETERS
----------

 `$attachment_id` 
:   ([*int*](/How_to_Pass_Tag_Parameters#Int "How to Pass Tag Parameters"))
    (*required*) Attachment ID for modification.
    Default: *None*

 `$args` 
:   ([*string|array*](/How_to_Pass_Tag_Parameters#String.7Carray "How to Pass Tag Parameters"))
    (*optional*) Optional. Override defaults.
    Default: null

ARGUMENTS
---------

 `errors` 
:   ([*array*](/How_to_Pass_Tag_Parameters#Array "How to Pass Tag Parameters"))
    (*optional*) Passed to get\_attachment\_fields\_to\_edit() by this
    function. Presumably used to change default error messages for
    default fields
    Default: null

 `send` 
:   ([*boolean*](/How_to_Pass_Tag_Parameters#Boolean "How to Pass Tag Parameters"))
    (*optional*) Whether to include the submit button html.
    Default: the result of conditional logic. Set to the result of
    post\_type\_supports( post-\>ID, 'editor' ) if the post has an ID.
    Or, if the post doesn't have an ID, "true".

 `delete` 
:   ([*boolean*](/How_to_Pass_Tag_Parameters#Boolean "How to Pass Tag Parameters"))
    (*optional*) Whether to include delete link html.
    Default: true

 `toggle` 
:   ([*boolean*](/How_to_Pass_Tag_Parameters#Boolean "How to Pass Tag Parameters"))
    (*optional*) Whether to include toggle link html.
    Default: true

 `show_title` 
:   ([*boolean*](/How_to_Pass_Tag_Parameters#Boolean "How to Pass Tag Parameters"))
    (*optional*) Whether to include attachment title html.
    Default: true

RETURN VALUES
-------------

 `` `(string)`{style="color:gray"} 
:   HTML form for attachment.

CHANGE LOG
----------

Since: [2.5](/Version_2.5 "Version 2.5")

SOURCE FILE
-----------

`get_media_item()` is located in `wp-admin/includes/media.php`

